ext-500 font-small line-clamp-2">Purpose &amp; context Sri is a solo founde=
r with no technical background building a privacy-first mobile app for food=
 ingredient scanning =E2=80=94 a personal food intelligence companion for p=
eople managing food sensitivities, intolerances, and dietary preferences. T=
he zero-budget constraint is active at this stage, and Claude is functionin=
g as the primary planning and development partner. The core locked proposit=
ion: the app reflects the user's own data back to them and never issues hea=
lth verdicts, brand rankings, safety labels, or consumption advice. It spea=
ks definitively only for allergen matches, observationally for patterns, an=
d never advisorily. The immediate day-one value is the allergen finder itse=
lf =E2=80=94 saving several minutes of manual label reading per product wit=
h immediate, personally relevant results. Reaction logging, pattern recogni=
tion, and predictive intelligence layer on top of that established trust an=
d habit. Sri has strong product instincts, consistently pushes back on over=
complication, and maintains a clear core proposition under pressure. Sri ha=
s explicitly requested a strictly informational and critical communication =
style =E2=80=94 direct identification of problems, contradictions, and unre=
solved decisions only, with no affirmations, ego-stroking, or complimentary=
 framing. --- Current state The session has moved through complete product =
architecture, compliance framework, technical stack selection, monetization=
 design, and feature prioritization across multiple product versions. A com=
prehensive context transfer note for Claude Code was requested at the end o=
f the session, but cannot be finalized until six open decisions are resolve=
d. Six blocking decisions before development begins: Whether goal alignment=
 flagging sits in the free tier or V1 paid tier Free tier calendar history =
boundary (full history vs. limited window) Family profile cap per account a=
nd whether child mode is V1 or V2 Whether V1 has a monthly pricing option o=
r annual only The exact free and V1 user experience after a scan =E2=80=94 =
emoji rating and reaction logging are confirmed V2 features, leaving free a=
nd V1 scans producing silent log entries with no engagement loop; this need=
s resolution Complete feature-to-tier entitlement table =E2=80=94 multiple =
unconfirmed assignments blocking schema sprint scope definition A pre-devel=
opment sprint dedicated entirely to training-ready schema design is confirm=
ed before any feature code is written. The schema sprint scope cannot be fu=
lly defined until the entitlement table is resolved. --- On the horizon Res=
olve the six open decisions above to finalize the Claude Code context trans=
fer note Execute the schema design sprint (one full sprint, training-ready,=
 before feature development) UT Dallas cross-validation of the allergen syn=
onym graph is planned Begin Claude Code development handoff once context tr=
ansfer note is complete and schema sprint is scoped --- Key learnings &amp;=
 principles The allergen finder is the core hook and must deliver value on =
day one before any log history exists =E2=80=94 all engagement features are=
 additive, not foundational The app must never issue advice, verdicts, or r=
ankings; informational framing is non-negotiable and must be enforced at th=
e architecture level, not just the UI level Overcomplication is a recurring=
 risk; Sri consistently trims scope to protect the core proposition Schema =
design must be training-ready from the start =E2=80=94 retrofitting will be=
 costly; this is why the dedicated pre-development sprint exists The featur=
e-to-tier entitlement table must be fully resolved before schema work begin=
s, as ambiguity here cascades into architectural debt --- Approach &amp; pa=
tterns Works through product decisions systematically and iteratively, lock=
ing confirmed decisions explicitly before moving on Generates living Word d=
ocuments as product records; v3.0 is the most current authoritative version=
 from the prior session Pushes back on feature creep and unnecessary comple=
xity in real time Uses Claude as a thought partner for architecture, compli=
ance, and prioritization, not just execution --- Tools &amp; resources Fram=
ework: React Native with Expo OCR: Google ML Kit V2 (on-device) Local stora=
ge: SQLite via WatermelonDB with SQLCipher Server storage: User-isolated en=
crypted partitions for persistent data Sync: WiFi-only; server authoritativ=
e on conflict Image retention: 7-day local auto-delete; all derived text da=
ta retained permanently on server Barcode decoding: Background silent decod=
ing for product name resolution only =E2=80=94 never surfaced to users Alle=
rgen matching: Two-layer architecture =E2=80=94 prioritized synonym graph c=
hecked first, then full 500=E2=80=931,000 ingredient database COPPA complia=
nce method: User-selected age input as good-faith compliance for child prof=
iles Monetization: 10 monthly scan tokens for free tier (no rollover); 12-d=
ay full-access free trial; V1 at $12/year; V2 at $23.99/year or $2.99/month=
 Validation: UT Dallas cross-validation of allergen synonym graph planned A=
ccount structure: Mandatory email for account recovery (separate disclosed =
onboarding screen, single explicit purpose statement); pseudonymous interna=
l account IDs</p><p class=3D"font-small text-text-500 opacity-60 pt-0.5">La=
